Discuss.<br>
<br>
This discussion is important.  Your input is needed here.<br>
<br>
Had this discussion started a week ago, I might have said, maybe, depends on the test.  However, after much thought on the issue, I'm inclined to say no.  The members will test the moderators' patience enough without the administration doing it too.  We have OQ sitting right here; so if anyone Administrator, moderator or member, has any issues with how a situation was handled it can be discussed and consensus can be reached.  Consensus might mean that the moderator or administrator handles the situation differently next time.  It might mean that the community felt the action was appropriate in the context.  We can start reminder threads about policies which haven't been exercised through lack of need.  I don't think the administration should manufacture situations that create more work for the moderators.<br>
<br>
HF wrote in the intro to the Episodes forum, &quot;Don't make more work for your mod, do NOT tear the mask off the old Lone Ranger, nor should you spit into the wind and forget about messing around with Jim...&quot; <br>
<br>
Good advice.  I think I can safely assume that we all have busy lives.  One doesn't encourage volunteers by making the job unecessarily annoying.  <br>
<br>
If the consensus is that testing should be implemented, I recommend that tests be limited to only a couple of threads per forum.  No moderator should have to deal with large amounts of extra work because of any test.  <br>
<br>
