<br>
I'm interested in seeing the Administration adhere to the principles of community consensus rather than instituting unilateral decisions on such issues.  The failure to ask for consensus has already cost us one valuable and appreciated moderator.  It shouldn't have.  I'd expect the Administration to adhere to the philosophy of consensus even more than the moderators.  They have a greater responsibility to do so because of their greater power.  <br>
<br>
So let's discuss the wisdom of testing and reach consensus.  The Administration should want and welcome such discussion from the community.  Ideally, an Administrator would have started this discussion in OQ before instigating any testing.  But, no one did.  Fine.  Let's take this incident as a learning experience and actually learn from it.  <br>
<br>
