&quot;4. No Admin may make changes to the board without consent of the other admins. <br>
<br>
5. All Admins must abide by the decisions of the membership on all issues, unless those decisions violate existing ezboard policy. The admins will make every effort to determine the ‘will of the members’ either by poll or a discussion thread that addresses the issue squarely.<br>
<br>
6. No Admin may create a secret forum, invisible forum or any forum that members cannot view/read. <br>
<br>
Administrators Responsibilities<br>
<br>
1. Admins are responsible for the viability of the board and for its expansion.<br>
<br>
2. Admins are responsible for their actions and their decisions. They can and will be held accountable for behavior that is contrary to the long-term viability of the board and or the health of the membership in general. <br>
<br>
3. Admins are responsible to the Moderators, community and its members.&quot;<br>
<br>
Unilateral decisions made by administrators violate a number of these stated policies.  Actions of some administrators on this board have already violated those policies.<br>
<br>
The statement below has also been added to the posted policy despite the fact that no community consensus or discussion took place regarding its addition.  This statement directly contradicts the above policy.<br>
<br>
&quot;These rules are subject to change at any time with the consensus of the Administration. &quot;  <br>
<br>
If the Administration can change the policy at their whim, then they aren't making every effort to determine the will of the members.<br>
