Anyway... I don't think the tests violate the policy, and I don't have a problem with the Admins right to start them.  I also don't like them.  It seems like a preposterous waste of time, in which not much is gained.  What would be more productive is an ACTUAL test - i.e... &quot;what would you do if...&quot;  which is something that would prompt a quick re-read of the policy (it seems that that's really the only thing that is at stake!).  Response time and accurate answers could be reported back to the moderator being tested, and objections to the policy (as worded) would then be raised as legitimate discussion.<br>
