<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://site.voila.fr/slipstreambbsexposed/index.html" target="top">SlipstreamBBS Exposed</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003B75><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bslipstreambbs12353.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xcaitriona>XCaitriona</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#0000FF, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='user title'>Triumvir</span></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 493<br> <font color=#EFD68C>(2/14/03 5:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fslipstreambbs12353frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.rhwolfe.com/avatar/cait.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Testing Moderators</span><hr size=1> Ok, I'll try...........<br>
<br>
If there was any discomfrot due to the testing I have already apologized on behalf of the Admins.<br>
<br>
BUT, and I mean this ...... Our only intent was to help Mods identify suitations and then act appropriately.  And all the test threads were marked TEST.<br>
<br>
We wanted to give you expereince.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>We had done it ourselves and found it useful.  It is as simple as that.]</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I still have not heard any suggestion from any of the Mods for another way for Mods to gain any practical experience once they have the Mod controls.  The point of the excercise that created this discussion was is still is-- a way to  give Mods practice.  And until this discussion focuses on THAT point I'm not inclined to abandon 'testing'.<br>
<br>
We can argue back and forth about who was right, who was wrong and who feels we shouldn't do it and who feels we should do it... BUT the point still remains we have to find a way to give practical experience to Mods so that when and if an attack hits we are prepared and act in concert.  I'd like each Mod to know exactly what to do and how to do it.. Instead of the panic that might ensue.<br>
<br>
Now, if someone feels they don't need this because they have experience on another board... that is fine.. because that demonstrates that they DO have experience.<br>
<br>
Like I said, I'd rather this got back to the issue of Mods and their practical hands on training.<br>
<br>
As to policy......... We had testing from the very beginning.  WE DID IT...... This isn't something new we sprung on Lil.  We had it from day #1...... And I dont' need to know each specific time a test might be done, because 'testing' had been standard operating form the beginning.  My first day with Admin controls, I was put through my paces, and I was greateful for it.  I learn quickly and I saw how easy it was.  I also saw how easy it was to make a mistake.  We felt from the beginning that this was a good tool and method and should be continued.  This was not something new or shocking~and and although this situation in particular turned out badly.. as a rule all the other tests were done and people had no complaints.  <br>
<br>
As to the 'waste of time' issue, is it a waste of time to learn your jobs?  I tend to think not.  If any of you has expereince then of course the issue becomes moot.  After all we're not trying to waste 'OUR' time either.  <br>
<br>
And  I agree that we need to listen to the Mods, but I also think that the Mods need to listen to us.  This was so harmless and ultimately even the harm it has done has brought practice.  Perhaps some of you feel that testing is too close a word to passing or failing.  Look at it like a lab where you are put in situations that require real repsonses.  It is and was that simple.<br>
<br>
Now, if anyone has a suggestion for how to gain this experience in another way, I am all ears.  But there has to be a way presented that does give practical expereince or we have to resort of choosing only mods who have experience on other boards, because without a way to gain experience under controlled circumstances, we have a wide open door to chaos.<br>
<br>
~ Cait <p>____________________________________<br>
<br>
&quot;I tore myself away from the safe comfort of certainties through my love for truth; and truth rewarded me. &quot; <br>
Simone de Beauvoir<br>
